ContentDesc_Zenit der Götter - Lakshmi: In the shadow of Kugane's renowned Mujikoza theater, you recount your clash with Sri Lakshmi to the wandering minstrel. Moved to melancholy by the tragic tale, he forgoes adapting it for the stage, choosing instead to honor the memory of the departed with a verse. So vivid are the words and sorrowful the melody, you cannot help but relive the fateful encounter in your mind's eye...
QuestName_Songs in the Key of Kugane: Songs in the Key of Kugane
instancecontenttextdata_ids_16301_Text: A sssliver of grace I bequeath to you...
instancecontenttextdata_ids_16302_Text: My grace, my beauty, my everything...is yours...
instancecontenttextdata_ids_16303_Text: I shall free you from your hate!
instancecontenttextdata_ids_16304_Text: Do you not long for releassse from this pain?
instancecontenttextdata_ids_16305_Text: There is no place for you within our dream...
instancecontenttextdata_ids_16306_Text: Only the faithful may know joy everlasssting...
instancecontenttextdata_ids_16308_Text: Ressst your weary sssouls in my bosom.
instancecontenttextdata_ids_16309_Text: Partake of my life and my love...
instancecontenttextdata_ids_16311_Text: Drink of me and cast out these tainted of light!
instancecontenttextdata_ids_16314_Text: Who are you to wake them from the dream...
